main: ^Reyes! What a surprise! What are you doing here?
^Hi Tia! I’m just here to give you some supplies. Mom sent me.
^Oh well come in, hija. We haven’t talked in a while.
ThatsWeird: ^Sorry, I wish I could stay, but I have to make a couple more deliveries.
^Oh ok hija! You’re so kind to your mom, helping her out with deliveries! You know, she told me you wanted to cut off all your hair!
^I was so worried about seeing you again, but it looks like you haven’t cut it. It’s so long and beautiful, I wish I had hair like that. Every girl dreams of long hair like you!
WhatTheHell: ^Yes, hija. She talks so much about you. And I talk to her about your late cousin as well. You know how parents are.
^Speaking of parents, you’re still single right? No surprises?
GoodMood: ^You already know I’m not looking for anyone Tia.
^Good, I was just making sure you’re being responsible. I know your Mom wants you to get a partner, but it’s too early for that, ok? Live your life and stay young for as long as possible.
^Of course, Tia. Thank you for always looking out for me.
TheDon: ^By the way, do you happen to know where Don Luis lives? Mom doesn’t know where he lives and we figured you might.
^Ah, Don Luis. I don’t know exactly where he lives, but he usually hangs out with his friends near the town square.
^Those guys are only good for the streets, you know. Don’t stay around them too long.
LetsGo: ^Well, uh , thank you, Tia. I’ll get going now, the bread is starting to get squished. I’ll come by and visit you soon! Say hi to everyone at home for me!
